      "description": "Compute Engine is still a core part of many real workloads. You’ll launch virtual machines, choose machine types and disks, use startup scripts, and manage images, instance groups, and autoscaling.",
      "title": "Virtual Machines with Compute Engine"
    },
    {
      "description": "Containers are a normal part of modern cloud work. This chapter covers container images, Artifact Registry, Cloud Run, and the tradeoffs between running containers serverlessly and on managed clusters.",
      "title": "Containers and Cloud Run"
